quran[12]{c,v,t,f}:
  97,1,"Indeed, We sent this [Qur’an] down on the Night of Decree<sup>1</sup>.","[1] The Qur’an was first revealed completely to the lowest heaven on this night. Also, its revelation on the Prophet (ﷺ) started on this night."
  97,2,"How do you know what the Night of Decree is?",""
  97,3,"The Night of Decree is better than a thousand months.",""
  97,4,"On that night the angels and the Spirit [i.e., Gabriel] descend by their Lord’s permission with all decrees<sup>2</sup>.","[2] Bringing down the exact provisions, life, death, and other things destined for the creatures for the coming year by Allah's permission."
  97,5,"It is all peace<sup>3</sup> until the break of dawn.","[3] Upon the believers."
  98,1,"Those who disbelieve from the People of the Book and the polytheists were not going to desist [from disbelief]<sup>1</sup> until there came to them clear proof,","[1] i.e., and from deviant ways."
  98,2,"a messenger from Allah, reciting pure pages<sup>2</sup>","[2] i.e., that contains no falsehood."
  98,3,"containing upright commandments.",""
  98,4,"Yet those who were given the Scripture did not disagree<sup>3</sup> except after the clear proof came to them,","[3] Into different sects and denominations."
  98,5,"although they were commanded only to worship Allah with sincere devotion to Him, being inclined to the true faith, and to establish prayer and give zakah; that is the true religion.",""
  98,6,"Those who disbelieve from the People of the Book and the polytheists will be in the fire of Hell, abiding therein forever. It is they who are the worst of creatures.",""
  98,7,"As for those who believe and do righteous deeds – it is they who are the best of creatures.",""
